# Executive summary

_Period: {{ period_start }} – {{ period_end }} ({{ n_periods }} periods)._

## Headline finding

{% if channels %}
{%- set top_channel = channels[0] %}
Across this period, paid media contributed an estimated
**{{ "{:,.0f}".format(total_media_contribution) }}** to the target.
{% if top_channel.confidence == "high" %}
**`{{ top_channel.name }}`** was the largest contributor at
**{{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_mean) }}**
({{ "{:.0%}".format(top_channel.share_of_effect) }} of media impact),
with a 95% credible interval of
{{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_hdi_low) }}–{{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_hdi_high) }}.
{% elif top_channel.confidence == "moderate" %}
The model's best point estimate is that **`{{ top_channel.name }}`** was the
largest contributor at {{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_mean) }}
({{ "{:.0%}".format(top_channel.share_of_effect) }} of media impact),
with a wide 95% credible interval of
{{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_hdi_low) }}–{{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_hdi_high) }}.
The ranking is plausible but not tight.
{% else %}
The largest point estimate is **`{{ top_channel.name }}`** at
{{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_mean) }}, but the data does not
strongly support that ranking — its 95% credible interval is
{{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_hdi_low) }}–{{ "{:,.0f}".format(top_channel.contribution_hdi_high) }}.
Treat the ordering as suggestive, not decided.
{% endif %}
{% else %}
No channel contributions were available for this run.
{% endif %}
